	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This is truly excellent news.  I always believed that you could use the simplier circuit from a Famicom A/V (a.k.a. New-style Famicom) in a NES Top Loader and get perfect video quality.  
<br />
<br />Now, if we had a similar schematic of the NES Top-loader's video output path, we could compare it and see how simple a modification needs to be.  The schematic for the video output of the Famicom AV is about as simple as you can get.  I assume that Nintendo either neglected to add the 560pf capacitator, used wrong resistor/capacitator values or introduced an interference causing element through bad traces.  It would be easier to trace the NES Top Loader's output because it does not use the inside of the PCB to run traces.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


